## Technical Patterns

### 1. DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)

**Description**:  
The DRY principle emphasizes reusing code instead of duplicating it. In Python, this can be achieved through functions, modules, and classes. Adhering to DRY reduces code complexity and makes maintenance easier.

**Implementation Notes**:  
- Ensure that functions and modules are well-documented and reusable.  
- Avoid duplicating logic across different parts of the codebase.

